   "id": "video_moment:tig-setup-with-foot-pedal-and-lift-arc-start",
   "type": "video_moment",
   "name": "TIG setup with foot pedal and lift-arc start",
   "summary": "The presenter sets up TIG welding with a foot pedal for amperage control, explaining that without high-frequency start, the lift-arc method is used: touching tungsten to the workpiece, stepping the pedal, then lifting to strike the arc; total setup including torch, tungsten grinding and gas hookup took about 8 minutes.",
